# Security, Env, and Secrets (Mandatory)

## Secrets and configuration

- Never commit real secrets, credentials, API keys, or tokens.
- Maintain `.env.example` with placeholder values only.
- Load runtime secrets from approved secure storage and environment variables.

## Logging and data exposure

- Never log passwords, session cookies, tokens, or sensitive personal data.
- Keep error messages safe for clients and place sensitive diagnostics in protected logs only.
- Do not include secrets in issue comments, PR descriptions, or commit messages.

## Transport and session security

- Use HTTPS/TLS for production traffic.
- Keep auth state in HTTP-only cookies and avoid client-side token persistence.

## Review gate

- Any change touching auth, env, or secrets handling requires explicit reviewer acknowledgement.
